Static variable :-	A). It can be accessed using class name.
  				  	B). Static variables can be accessed by static and non static methods.
  				  	c). Static variables reduce the amount of memory used by a program.
  				  	D). Static variables are shared among all instances of a class.
  				  	E). Static variable is like a global variable and is available to all methods.

School classroom example -> Class Number, Class teacher, subjects, etc.

	 
	
	
Non-static variable :-	A). Non static variables can be accessed using instance of a class.
						B). Non static variables cannot be accessed inside a static method directly.
						c). Non static variables do not reduce the amount of memory used by a program.
						D). Non static variables are specific to that instance of a class.
						E). Non static variable is like a local variable and they can be accessed through only instance of a class.

School classroom example -> Student name, roll number, marks etc.



		
						
						
						
						
			  	
  				  	